                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jonathan.melnick",
                        "name": "jonathan.melnick",
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Melnick",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This issue still affects version 1.7.8 !!\n\nThe bug also occurs if param's value is false.\n\nBy any means, this is not minor!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jonathan.melnick",
                        "name": "jonathan.melnick",
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Melnick",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-07T03:38:10.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-07T03:38:10.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30028",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=oximoron",
                        "name": "oximoron",
                        "displayName": "Harro van der Klauw",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The params come from the url, so technically they will always be strings, the number 0 and a boolean value aren't really possible to be part of the params.\n\n\nbut I agree that for sanity's sake it should be fixed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=oximoron",
                        "name": "oximoron",
                        "displayName": "Harro van der Klauw",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-08T05:17:30.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-08T05:17:30.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30029",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cjne",
                        "name": "cjne",
                        "displayName": "Johan Isacsson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In my case i was setting values in one action using _setParam and then used _getParam in another action, so it does not always have to come from the URL.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=cjne",
                        "name": "cjne",
                        "displayName": "Johan Isacsson",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-08T05:28:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-08T05:28:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36147",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=megar",
                        "name": "megar",
                        "displayName": "Gilles Bouthenot",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is a MAJOR issue !\r\n\r\nAs proposed the simple patch\r\nif ((null == $value) && (null !== $default)) {\r\n\r\n->\r\n\r\nif ((null === $value) && (null !== $default)) {\r\n\r\nFixes it.\r\nProblem with 0 and \"\", both handled like param not present.\r\n\r\nPlease fix it ASAP.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=megar",
                        "name": "megar",
                        "displayName": "Gilles Bouthenot",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-19T06:24:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-19T06:24:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36932",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mluiten",
                        "name": "mluiten",
                        "displayName": "Menno Luiten",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Attached (simple) patch implementing the suggested solution, if this is deemed a bug by upstream. I would suggest it is.\r\n\r\n~My CLA has been submitted, -but not yet processed-~",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mluiten",
                        "name": "mluiten",
                        "displayName": "Menno Luiten",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-15T05:12:24.000+0000",
